  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7036.92 sitting between the max negative gamma pocket at 7015 (-1653.1M) and the massive positive gamma wall at 7050 (+12008.2M), dealers are currently in a neutral hedging stance but approaching significant selling pressure. The \"wall_break\" event detection combined with the 5.2% 5-minute move suggests we're testing the critical 7050 resistance where dealers will aggressively sell rallies into any push higher. Given the PIN regime and proximity to max positive gamma, expect strong mean reversion dynamics with dealers providing liquidity against momentum—selling any break above 7050 and buying dips back toward 7015-7030 support cluster.\n\n**Bottom line:** Price should face heavy selling pressure near 7050 and get pushed back toward 7000-7030.",
